    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it makes so much sense. i've been thinking, if they were masking things in the photos, they probably had to manipulate the telemetry data too, right? like, if the sensors picked up something massive or anomalous near the lunar landing site, they'd have to rewrite the signal logs so it just looks like static or standard background noise. do you think there's any way to cross-reference the original raw signal data with the later \"official\" versions to see where the numbers were fudged?",
